{"lemma":"بُهْتانِ","slug":"بُهْتانِ","root":"ب.ه.ت","root_slug":"ب-ه-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ه-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بُهْتان","root":"بهت","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3389"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%87%D9%92%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَهَتَ (bahata) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vilification, defamation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lying, invective"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of بَهَتَ (bahata)."},"ipa":["/buh.taːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3389","headword_ar":"بُهْتَانٌ","root":"bht","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahiytapN","text_ar":"بَهِيتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same [when the former is used as a subst.; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calumny, slander,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"false accusation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A, Msb: [see 1:]) or both signify, the former as explained by Aboo-Is-hák, and the latter as explained in the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a falsehood by reason of which one is confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, and unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA; [in which it seems to be indicated that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buhotN","text_ar":"بُهْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same;]) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albahotu","text_ar":"البَهْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning “ the being confounded ” &c.: (Aboo-Is-hák, TA:) the former is a subst. signifying [also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a false accusation of adultery"},{"kind":"text","text":"against a woman; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a forgery of a lie"},{"kind":"text","text":"against her: (Msb:) and ↓ the latter, [and the former also, simply,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lie,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falsehood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buhotN","text_ar":"بُهْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahotN","text_ar":"بَهْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buhotaAnFA waA_ivomFA mubiynFA","text_ar":"بُهْتَانًا وَاـِثْمًا مُبِينًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur iv. 24, is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Falsely accusing of adultery, and acting in a manifestly sinful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"criminal manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting wrongfully"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Bd, Jel.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAhu biAlbahiytapi","text_ar":"رَمَاهُ بِالبَهِيتَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He accused him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of, calumny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA illobahiytapi","text_ar":"يَا ِللْبَهِيتَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the [prep.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O,"},{"kind":"text","text":"come to my aid, or succour,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on account of the calumny!"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; for it is] a phrase used in calling for aid, or succour. (S.) [And if you would express wonder, you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA allobahiytapi","text_ar":"يَا َللْبَهِيتَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O the calumny!"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}